      <method id="StopCalculationExecution" name="POST">
        <doc title="StopCalculationExecution" xml:lang="en">&lt;p&gt;Requests the cancellation of a calculation. A &lt;code&gt;StopCalculationExecution&lt;/code&gt; call on a calculation that is already in a terminal state (for example, &lt;code&gt;STOPPED&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;FAILED&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;COMPLETED&lt;/code&gt;) succeeds but has no effect.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;note&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cancelling a calculation is done on a best effort basis. If a calculation cannot be cancelled, you can be charged for its completion. If you are concerned about being charged for a calculation that cannot be cancelled, consider terminating the session in which the calculation is running.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/note&gt;</doc>
